	damon_sysfs_schemes_clear_regions(
			sysfs_kdamond->contexts->contexts_arr[0]->schemes);
	return damos_walk(ctx, &control);
}
```

If `sysfs_kdamond->contexts->nr == 0`, `contexts_arr` is NULL, confirming the null pointer dereference vulnerability!

The author added the check `if (sysfs_kdamond->contexts->nr != 1)` ONLY to `damon_sysfs_repeat_call_fn`, but the exact same functions are executed via `damon_sysfs_damon_call` (by `state_store`)!

For example, in `damon_sysfs_upd_schemes_stats`:

```c
static int damon_sysfs_upd_schemes_stats(void *data)
{
	struct damon_sysfs_kdamond *kdamond = data;
	struct damon_ctx *ctx = kdamond->damon_ctx;

	damon_sysfs_schemes_update_stats(
			kdamond->contexts->contexts_arr[0]->schemes, ctx);
	return 0;
}
```

If called from `state_store` when `nr` is 0, it WILL CRASH!

